link: G. C. Greubel, Table of n, a(n) for n = -1..1000
D. Ford, J. McKay and S. P. Norton, More on replicable functions, Commun. Algebra 22, No. 13, 5175-5193 (1994).
Index entries for McKay-Thompson series for Monster simple group
formula: Expansion of A - 4 + 1/A, where A = (eta(q^2)*eta(q^7)/(eta(q)*eta(q^14) ))^4, in powers of q. - _G. C. Greubel_, Jun 18 2018
mathematica: eta[q_]:= q^(1/24)*QPochhammer[q]; e14C := (eta[q^2]*eta[q^7]/(eta[q] *eta[q^14]))^4; a:= CoefficientList[Series[-4 + e14C + 1/e14C, {q, 0, 60}], q]; Table[a[[n]], {n, 1, 50}] (* _G. C. Greubel_, Jun 18 2018 *)
program: (PARI) q='q+O('q^50); A = (eta(q^2)*eta(q^7)/(eta(q)*eta(q^14) ))^4/q; Vec(A - 4 + 1/A) \\ _G. C. Greubel_, Jun 18 2018
